message:
Finished up lens calibration code. Moved the majority of it into a new class to clean up the camera class.
Switched ReferenceCamera image transforms to use OpenCV, speeding things up.
Fixes #226.

Finished up lens calibration code. Moved the majority of it into a new class to clean up the camera class.
Switched ReferenceCamera image transforms to use OpenCV, speeding things up.
Fixes #226.
Dump the camera matrix and distortion coeffs from the wizard. No real reason to ever show or edit these and it's ugly code.
Started working on adding the 2 camera view option to the camera panel. Not quite finished, the pref is not loading properly.

Disable calibration at start of calibration.
Improve instructions.
Apply Calibration? checkbox now updates live.
nu.pattern loader

changed location() 

Difference between official and used Location

vision Utils.java stripped down

It allows to call external program , including python to find part.
usage example
bottomLocation = parseLoc(callImg("/usr/bin/python","bottom.py",part, toMat(camera.capture()), null);

Revert back to 9ea0b4f650e5b282d5e99d72f0f399c1a07ece8e with 9957a732af2fa9ca5fd226069e72b664b4d1d481 cherry picked. The revert is due to a major regression documented at https://github.com/openpnp/openpnp/issues/220
Fix a concurrent modification exception when iterating solutions.

Adds replan functionality to JobPlanner and friends. This allows the caller to push a previously planned placement solution back into the queue to try again. More explanation in the comments.
Update ReferenceJobProcessor to use the new replan functionality and fix a number of issues where showing the user would result in an aborted job.
The change additionally makes it so that when a feed failure happens the feeder is disabled and the processor tries again. The user is only notified if no feeder is eventually found.
All in all, this fixes #206.
Don't have the ReferenceNozzleTip blow up if it can't find a previously reference part. Just quietly remove it.

SimpleJobPlanner will now return partial solutions when no viable feeder or nozzle tip is found. This allows the processor to show the correct error message in these conditions. This is the first step in fixing several issues. This fixes #120, specifically with more to come.
JobPanel now force sets a JobProcessor when one is loaded, instead of relying on the tab listener to set it. This fixes #168.

Add new "position nozzle without safe z" button option to location buttons panel and enable it for the nozzle tip wizard. This fixes #190.
Fixed copy and paste icons which were the wrong size.
Dumped the .idraw and .svg versions of the full icon sheet as these contained all the wrong sizes of icons. Better to just manage the icons individually.

OpenBuilds driver now calculates it's Z position for comparison in degrees instead of... not at all. Fixes #95.
Fixes a bug where when using spring loaded homing the Z would not reset correctly when it is extended.
Fixes a homing timeout bug.

Fixes #167 (again) by enabling timeouts in the OpenBuilds driver. Also converted the driver to the newer LinkedBlockingQueue model.
Changed default timeout for commands in the OpenBuilds driver to 5 seconds instead of forever.
Changed home to allow 60 seconds to timeout because of the above.

Fixes #193, setEnabled is now called in it's own thread instead of on the machine task queue. This keeps emergency stop situations from getting queued and putting it in it's own thread keeps it from blocking the UI.
Fixes #203, actuators can now be attached directly to the machine and the appropriate APIs are available on Machine.

Reworked jog controls panel to provide better controls along with adding axis specific zero buttons.
Moved the home button up into the jog controls panel.
Moved the show jog controls menu option from View to Machine as I think this is where people will tend to look for it.
Added lots of new material design icons.
Removed the Move to 0 menu option since this was a area of trouble for some people and now we have per axis controls for it.
Fixes #129 - When you click the configure feeder button on the placements table you are now either shown the feeder if it exists or shown the new feeder dialog so you can create one.
Removing the continuous editing hack until I can make it work better. Right now it starts editing just by clicking on a cell and it's annoying.
Fixes #209, capture camera location in location buttons no longer updates Z.
